It includes 242 given two stars, 255 one star and six given no stars at all. A further 1,467 are only 'generally satisfactory'. The ratings are awarded by council inspectors.

Luciana Berger, Labour's shadow public health minister, said: 'It is not acceptable that over 500 hospitals, childcare and caring premises have been told to improve their food hygiene.

'Everyone using these public services should have the right to expect food that has been prepared safely, in a clean environment.

'The Government must hold these premises to account on the urgent action they must now take to address these serious failings in standards.'

